author: Rob Woodfork
title: NFL Week 7 Recap
text:
Home » News » Sports » NFL Week 7 Recap NFL Week 7 Recap By Rob Woodfork October 26, 2015 2:00 am An epic comeback, the feel-good story of the year and a Madden-esque beatdown. It was anything but a lucky (Week) 7 in the NFL. Yeah, we liked that. (via @CSNMA ) https://t.co/hjDwrnxPq2 — Washington Redskins (@Redskins) October 25, 2015 
Buccaneers 30 
This is a whole lotta swag for a guy who watches HGTV … 
But for real … the ‘Skins franchise-record 24-point comeback improves them to 3-3 in their 6th annual (and wholly unnecessary) homecoming weekend and essentially saves their season. If they can keep Jordan Reed healthy and Cousins’ confidence up, they might just have something on the other end of their bye week (after their certain loss in New England, that is).
